    "Experimentally, prototype implementations using acoustic metamaterials or other passive wave-based structures could enable direct analog inference on real sound signals, paving the way for low-power edge computing and passive acoustic sensing in environments where electronic systems face limitations.Overall, this work provides both theoretical foundations and practical design principles for acoustic neural networks, demonstrating that neural computation can, in principle, be achieved through the physics of sound.",
